        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32723",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Could you please explain in (way) more detail what you mean?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-07-20T07:32:33.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-07-20T07:32:33.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32724",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Dolf -- I asked him to post this based on an exchange on-list.\n\nBasically, there is code like the following in the decorator:\n{code}\n$this->removeOption('noAttribs')\n     ->removeOption('openOnly')\n     ->removeOption('closeOnly');\n{code}\nwhich is used to ensure that certain options do not clutter the HTML. The problem is that on subsequent calls, the decorator will no longer remember those settings, as they've now been removed. The better course of action is to grab all options, and in the returned array, selectively remove those which are not necessary.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-07-20T07:48:59.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-07-20T07:48:59.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32728",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mathk",
                        "name": "mathk",
                        "displayName": "Mathieu Suen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Why not hook in the constructor and grab those option in some instances variables?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mathk",
                        "name": "mathk",
                        "displayName": "Mathieu Suen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-07-20T08:11:23.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-07-20T08:11:23.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32729",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "@mathieu: Because options can be set *after* instantiation as well:\n{code}\n$htmlTag = $element->getDecorator('row')->setOption('noAttribs', true);\n{code}\nIt needs to be done at render() time.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-07-20T08:24:19.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-07-20T08:24:19.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32730",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mathk",
                        "name": "mathk",
                        "displayName": "Mathieu Suen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Ok.\nIMHO I would rather not mix-up html options and tags specific option.\n\nJust use some setting method:\n$element->getDecorator('row')->displayAttribs(bool);\n...",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mathk",
                        "name": "mathk",
                        "displayName": "Mathieu Suen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-07-20T08:48:34.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-07-20T08:48:34.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
    },
